wiki.summary: “A$AP Forever” is the first official single released from Rocky’s upcoming album TESTING. Flacko first premiered this song on Fallon Tonight along with the track Distorted Records, and dropped its video shortly after. The track details Rocky’s loyalty to his crew, the A$AP Mob. The name possibly refers to an album of another great New York rap collective, being Wu-Tang Forever by the Wu-Tang Clan. It features a collaboration with Moby, who is a DJ known for his based electronic music. Read more on Last.fm.
wiki.content: “A$AP Forever” is the first official single released from Rocky’s upcoming album TESTING. Flacko first premiered this song on Fallon Tonight along with the track Distorted Records, and dropped its video shortly after. The track details Rocky’s loyalty to his crew, the A$AP Mob. The name possibly refers to an album of another great New York rap collective, being Wu-Tang Forever by the Wu-Tang Clan. It features a collaboration with Moby, who is a DJ known for his based electronic music. The song also heavily samples one of Moby’s songs “Porcelain.” Rocky had previously previewed this track before on an Instagram live. Though no tracklist has been released Rocky hinted that this would be the opening track to his long-awaited third album. A$AP Forever debuted in the top #60's on Billboard upon its release.
